{"pid":"0127277cd7f61c08165797dea3a831c9c1510680","tid":1753542,"uid":43070,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:18:43.000Z","msg":"推"},{"pid":"12c7c3bbf80e50d0d2b7a4820e9473a4a701f53f","tid":1753542,"uid":261627,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:19:25.000Z","msg":"可以點"},{"pid":"d730838534a5dc98c37a0cb639cff2384edb284d","tid":1753542,"uid":10419,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:19:31.000Z","msg":"Push"},{"pid":"f3d9a53b0b8046454fccc9e1f21d45a900c43906","tid":1753542,"uid":319616,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:19:52.000Z","msg":"短裙妹表示：推呀 需要記者 街坊！！！<br />\n街坊快啲入飛雁幼稚園<br />\n啲問題票真係好撚有問題！！！"},{"pid":"19850fcd57ca1004d0ce3493feabc93e795e6291","tid":1753542,"uid":120458,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:21:54.000Z","msg":"Dear Sir/ Madam,<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI am writing to lodge a complaint against vote counting malpractice occurred to the Lam Tin Constituency (Constituency Code: J19) of the District Council Election held on 24 November 2019.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThere are two candidates running for the District Council Election of the Lam Tin Constituency, namely KAN Ming Tung (Candidate Number 1) and FUNG Tak Sum (Candidate Number 2).<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThe two polling stations of the Lam Tin Constituency are SKH Tak Tin Lee Shiu Keung Primary School (Code: J1901) and Fei Ngan Kindergarten (Code: J1902).<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThe first round of vote counting ended at approximately 3:49am on 25 November 2019. The total number of votes for KAN Ming Tung was 4081, while that for FUNG Tak Sum was 4032. The total number of invalid votes was 65.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nHowever, it was revealed that the number of votes from the J1902 polling station was inconsistent with the number of voters. In light of the discrepancy, a second counting took place at approximately 4:31am. An election lawyer arrived at the station at approximately 7:12 am to explain relevant statutes, however the issue remained unsettled. A third counting took place at approximately 8:08am. &nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI point to you that the staff at the J1902 polling station miscounted the invalid votes and included them in the results for KAN Ming Tung. The staff also declined to make public its counting process.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nIn light of the faulted counting process, I demand a re-election for the Lam Tin Constituency of the 2019 District Council Election. Alternatively or at the same time, I request a re-counting that takes place publicly and that is supervised by independent third parties to ensure transparency of the election.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI look forward to your reply.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nYours faithfully,<br />\nXXX<br />\nDated this 25 November 2019."},{"pid":"f99ad3041dfae99ac4c0247bcc8740328784a89a","tid":1753542,"uid":120458,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"19850fcd57ca1004d0ce3493feabc93e795e6291","tid":1753542,"uid":120458,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:21:54.000Z","msg":"Dear Sir/ Madam,<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI am writing to lodge a complaint against vote counting malpractice occurred to the Lam Tin Constituency (Constituency Code: J19) of the District Council Election held on 24 November 2019.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThere are two candidates running for the District Council Election of the Lam Tin Constituency, namely KAN Ming Tung (Candidate Number 1) and FUNG Tak Sum (Candidate Number 2).<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThe two polling stations of the Lam Tin Constituency are SKH Tak Tin Lee Shiu Keung Primary School (Code: J1901) and Fei Ngan Kindergarten (Code: J1902).<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThe first round of vote counting ended at approximately 3:49am on 25 November 2019. The total number of votes for KAN Ming Tung was 4081, while that for FUNG Tak Sum was 4032. The total number of invalid votes was 65.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nHowever, it was revealed that the number of votes from the J1902 polling station was inconsistent with the number of voters. In light of the discrepancy, a second counting took place at approximately 4:31am. An election lawyer arrived at the station at approximately 7:12 am to explain relevant statutes, however the issue remained unsettled. A third counting took place at approximately 8:08am. &nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI point to you that the staff at the J1902 polling station miscounted the invalid votes and included them in the results for KAN Ming Tung. The staff also declined to make public its counting process.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nIn light of the faulted counting process, I demand a re-election for the Lam Tin Constituency of the 2019 District Council Election. Alternatively or at the same time, I request a re-counting that takes place publicly and that is supervised by independent third parties to ensure transparency of the election.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nI look forward to your reply.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nYours faithfully,<br />\nXXX<br />\nDated this 25 November 2019."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:22:07.000Z","msg":"快啲send出去"},{"pid":"6b93386ca2c80085fcbc57b9628ba83db1a0fc9e","tid":1753542,"uid":263435,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:23:24.000Z","msg":"點解冇左個回覆，再推"},{"pid":"c11728986e9889d398672925d06ea0ae0568c5bc","tid":1753542,"uid":131125,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:25:40.000Z","msg":"幫推"},{"pid":"fbdcec0e3f57de9ed8dcdfdada77c536da617f29","tid":1753542,"uid":54959,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-25T04:27:54.000Z","msg":"推<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"efb6578199b9b8bde500aab9b034cf2b344cbe54","tid":1753542,"uid":207968,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"rep